    "summary": "This paper studies the triangular Kondo lattice compound CePtAl4Ge2 using site-selective 27Al NMR to resolve the local magnetic environment of two inequivalent Al sites. By combining quadrupole analysis, Knight shifts, and spin-lattice relaxation, the authors show that the low-energy spin dynamics are strongly anisotropic and predominantly in-plane, with enhanced antiferromagnetic fluctuations that grow toward the Néel transition and are shaped by hyperfine form-factor filtering.",
    "measurement_types": [
      "27Al NMR spectra",
      "Knight shift analysis",
      "spin-lattice relaxation (T1) measurements",
      "magnetic susceptibility (from prior work)",
      "resistivity (from prior work)",
      "X-ray diffraction",
      "energy-dispersive x-ray spectroscopy",
      "electronic structure calculations (FLAPW/LDA)",
      "neutron diffraction (from prior work)"
    ],
